<file path="agentic/knowledge/webflow-mcp-capabilities.md">
 1: # Webflow MCP Capabilities
 2: 
 3: Verified: 2026-06-03. Source: `https://github.com/webflow/mcp-server` (`src/tools/deElement.ts`, `rules.ts`).
 4: 
 5: ---
 6: 
 7: ## element_builder
 8: 
 9: **Verified:** accepts `parent_element_id` to target a specific parent node.
10: 
11: ```typescript
12: // Per action in the actions[] array:
13: {
14:   build_label?: string;                    // optional label for result identification
15:   parent_element_id: {                     // REQUIRED — where to insert
16:     component: string;                     // component ID of target parent
17:     element:   string;                     // element ID of target parent
18:   };
19:   creation_position: "append" | "prepend" | "before" | "after";  // REQUIRED
20:   element_schema: DEElementSchema & {      // REQUIRED — element to create
21:     children?: element_schema[];           // recursive, optional
22:   };
23:   return_element_info?: boolean;           // return full element info if true
24: }
25: ```
26: 
27: **Implication for Phase 2B:** parent operator captures `{component, element}` from each section
28: container created in Phase 2A, stores as `target_parent_element_id` in blueprint + state.json,
29: passes as `parent_element_id` directly to `element_builder` calls inside each section-builder subagent.
30: 
31: ---
32: 
33: ## element_tool
34: 
35: Manipulates existing elements. Key operations:
36: - `get_all_elements`, `get_selected_element`, `select_element`
37: - `add_or_update_attribute`, `remove_attribute`, `update_id_attribute`
38: - `set_text`, `set_style`, `set_link`, `set_heading_level`, `set_image_asset`
39: - `remove_element`
40: - `query_elements` — query by ID, type, text, style, tag, attributes, component name
41: 
42: All tools require `siteId`.
43: 
44: ---
45: 
46: ## style_tool
47: 
48: Creates/updates/queries CSS styles at the style-definition level. Actions:
49: - `create_style` — create style with name and CSS properties
50: - `get_styles` — retrieve with filtering/breakpoint options
51: - `update_style` — modify existing
52: - `remove_style` — delete
53: - `query_styles` (BETA) — query by name path, ID, or CSS properties
54: 
55: Operates on style definitions only — does not apply styles to specific elements.
56: 
57: ---
58: 
59: ## whtml_builder
60: 
61: **FORBIDDEN in this workspace.** Inserts HTML/CSS markup. Parameters: `parent_element_id`,
62: `creation_position`, `html`, `css`, `get_children_info`. Off-limits per operating rules.
63: 
64: ---
65: 
66: ## Concurrent Write Capability
67: 
68: **Status: unconfirmed.** No explicit concurrent-write limitations, session restrictions, or
69: multi-agent conflict-resolution mechanisms are documented in `rules.ts` or source code.
70: 
71: **Design consequence:** Phase 2B (parallel-section-build) is designed to degrade gracefully:
72: - If MCP allows concurrent writes from multiple subagent sessions → true parallel builds.
73: - If MCP serializes writes at the Designer layer → sections build sequentially.
74: - Correctness is identical either way; parallelism is a performance property only.
75: 
76: **To confirm:** call `webflow_guide_tool` in a live session or test two simultaneous
77: `element_builder` calls targeting the same site from different subagent contexts.
78: 
79: ---
80: 
81: ## Naming Convention Used in Codebase
82: 
83: | Our field name | Webflow MCP param | Type |
84: |---|---|---|
85: | `parent_element_id` | `parent_element_id` | `{component: string, element: string}` |
86: | `target_parent_element_id` (blueprint) | — | stored reference, same shape |
87: | `site_id` | `siteId` | string |
88: 
89: All schemas updated to use `parent_element_id` with `{component, element}` structure.
90: Previous name `parent_node_id` was incorrect and has been replaced everywhere.
</file>

