<file path="agentic/policies/no-overwrite-policy.md">
 1: # No-Overwrite Policy
 2: 
 3: Default write mode is `create_only`.
 4: 
 5: Allowed write modes:
 6: 
 7: | Mode | Meaning |
 8: |---|---|
 9: | `create_only` | Create only when path does not exist. |
10: | `append_with_evidence` | Append a dated note with source and validation. |
11: | `merge_with_report` | Edit existing file only after reading it and reporting changed sections. |
12: | `manual` | Human performs or approves the write. |
13: 
14: Forbidden:
15: 
16: - silent overwrite,
17: - deleting workspace state without archive validation,
18: - restoring archives into non-empty workspace,
19: - writing secrets to committed files.
</file>

<file path="agentic/policies/tool-risk-levels.md">
 1: # Tool Risk Levels
 2: 
 3: | Class | Meaning | Default Policy |
 4: |---|---|---|
 5: | R0 | Local read-only inspection. | allow |
 6: | R1 | Local write inside this folder. | ask unless create-only scaffold or approved workflow file. |
 7: | R2 | External read from Figma/Webflow or web. | ask and log source. |
 8: | R3 | External write to Webflow or messaging tools. | explicit approval per phase and target. |
 9: | R4 | Destructive, archive/delete/restore, secrets, production data. | deny unless explicitly approved and validated. |
10: 
11: Every tool and MCP server must include `risk_class`, approval policy, auth requirements, allowed agents, and validation.
</file>

