<file path="agentic/knowledge/token-sync-architecture.md">
  1: # Token Sync Architecture
  2: 
  3: Tài liệu này giải thích cơ chế đồng bộ design token giữa **Figma → Repo → Webflow**
  4: và những điều kiện bắt buộc để pipeline MAS hoạt động deterministic.
  5: 
  6: ---
  7: 
  8: ## Nguyên tắc cốt lõi
  9: 
 10: > **Class definition = immutable. Token value = payload duy nhất cần sync.**
 11: 
 12: ```
 13: class text-weight-bold  →  var --font-weight--bold  →  value (project A: 700, project B: 900)
 14:        (không đổi)               (key cố định)              (thay đổi theo dự án/thiết kế)
 15: ```
 16: 
 17: `text-weight-bold` không bao giờ đổi tên hay nghĩa.
 18: Cái thay đổi là **giá trị của variable** đứng sau nó.
 19: LLM không đoán "bold là bao nhiêu" — nó đọc value từ token catalog.
 20: 
 21: ---
 22: 
 23: ## Kiến trúc 3-way ledger
 24: 
 25: ```
 26: ┌─────────────────┐      read       ┌──────────────────┐      push       ┌─────────────────┐
 27: │  Figma Project  │ ─────────────►  │   Repo Library   │ ─────────────►  │ Webflow Project │
 28: │  (design SoT)   │                 │ (git-versioned)  │                 │ (build target)  │
 29: │                 │                 │                  │                 │                 │
 30: │ Variables panel │                 │ libraries/       │                 │ Variables panel │
 31: │ - Base tokens   │ ◄─── drift? ──► │ {site_id}/       │ ◄─── drift? ──► │ - same tokens   │
 32: │ - Theme aliases │                 │ library.json     │                 │ - applied live  │
 33: └─────────────────┘                 │ token-map.json   │                 └─────────────────┘
 34:                                     │ changelog.json   │
 35:                                     └──────────────────┘
 36: ```
 37: 
 38: **Figma** = nơi designer định nghĩa token value.
 39: **Repo** = ledger trung gian, git-versioned, là nguồn sự thật cho agent build.
 40: **Webflow** = đích build, nhận value từ repo qua `variable_tool`.
 41: 
 42: Mỗi lần sync tạo 1 entry trong `changelog.json` — đây là audit trail.
 43: 
 44: ---
 45: 
 46: ## Token là "hợp đồng" giữa designer và LLM
 47: 
 48: | | Figma | Repo | Webflow |
 49: |---|---|---|---|
 50: | **Key (cố định)** | `Font Weight/bold` | `figma-token-map.json` mapping | `--font-weight--bold` |
 51: | **Value (sync được)** | 700 | `client-first-library.json` | variable value |
 52: 
 53: Designer đổi `Font Weight/bold` từ 700 → 900 ở Figma
 54: → `update_library_from_figma.py` cập nhật repo
 55: → `sync_library_to_webflow.py` push lên Webflow variable
 56: → **class `text-weight-bold` không cần đổi một chữ.**
 57: 
 58: ---
 59: 
 60: ## Điều kiện sống còn: designer BẮT BUỘC dùng Figma Variables
 61: 
 62: Đây là điều kiện kỹ thuật, không phải khuyến nghị.
 63: 
 64: | Designer làm | Kết quả pipeline |
 65: |---|---|
 66: | Dùng Variable cho color, spacing, typography | Token có thể sync → LLM deterministic |
 67: | Hardcode raw value (vd: `font-weight: 700` trực tiếp) | Không có token để sync → LLM phải đoán → vỡ |
 68: 
 69: **Pre-flight gate** tại bước ingest:
 70: - Phát hiện Figma node có raw value không backed-by-variable
 71: - Flag: `untokenized_property` → chặn pipeline hoặc yêu cầu designer fix trước
 72: - Không có cách tự động giải quyết case này — chỉ có kỷ luật đầu vào
 73: 
 74: ---
 75: 
 76: ## Vị trí trong pipeline MAS
 77: 
 78: ```
 79: Step 1  sync-library     ← TOKEN SYNC (đây)
 80:           │ Figma vars → repo → Webflow vars + drift gate + untokenized gate
 81:           │
 82: Step 2  sync-components  ← component structure map (de_component_tool)
 83:           │
 84: Step 3  read + html      ← read-figma-data.md → archive/deprecated-workflows/write-html-contract.webflow-first.md
 85:           │
 86: Step 4  split sections   ← section boundary detection
 87:           │
 88: Step 5  subagents build  ← parallel-section-build (apply-only)
 89: ```
 90: 
 91: Step 1 là nền. Nếu token-layer chuẩn, steps 3–5 hoàn toàn deterministic.
 92: 
 93: ---
 94: 
 95: ## Scripts hiện có
 96: 
 97: | Script | Việc làm |
 98: |---|---|
 99: | `scripts/update_library_from_figma.py` | Figma MCP → repo library (step: Figma→Repo) |
100: | `scripts/sync_library_to_webflow.py` | Repo → Webflow variable_tool (step: Repo→Webflow) |
101: | `tools/library_resolver.py` | Load/register/scaffold library dir, update last-synced |
102: | `scripts/gates/validate_project_library.py` | Gate: validate library JSON, class←→token coverage |
103: 
104: **Còn thiếu (v0.7.0 candidates):**
105: - `scripts/detect_token_drift.py` — so sánh 3-way (Figma ↔ repo ↔ Webflow), tạo reconciliation report
106: - `scripts/gates/validate_tokens_in_figma.py` — gate phát hiện untokenized property trong raw Figma data
107: 
108: ---
109: 
110: ## Hướng dẫn ngắn cho từng bên
111: 
112: ### Designer (Figma side)
113: - **Luôn dùng Variables** cho mọi color, spacing, typography, border — kể cả prototype
114: - Đặt tên variable theo pattern đã có: `Font Weight/bold`, `Spacing/medium`, `Colors/Theme/Text Color/primary`
115: - Không apply raw hex hoặc raw number trực tiếp lên element nếu nó sẽ xuất hiện trong component build
116: - Nếu muốn thêm token mới → thêm vào Figma Variable collection trước, đặt tên rõ ràng, rồi báo operator sync
117: 
118: ### Operator / Developer (repo side)
119: 1. Sau khi designer update token ở Figma → chạy `update_library_from_figma.py` để pull về repo
120: 2. Review `changelog.json` diff — confirm intentional changes
121: 3. Chạy `validate_project_library.py` để đảm bảo không có class mồ côi
122: 4. Chạy `sync_library_to_webflow.py` để push lên Webflow variable
123: 5. Commit repo
124: 
125: ### LLM / Agent (build side)
126: - Trước khi viết HTML contract → đọc `knowledge-base/libraries/{site_id}/client-first-library.json`
127: - Mọi color đều phải trace về token class (`text-color-primary`) — không hardcode hex
128: - Mọi spacing đều pick token (`margin-medium`, `gap-large`) — không compute px/16
129: - Nếu Figma node có raw value không có token → `flag: untokenized` trong design analysis, STOP
130: 
131: ---
132: 
133: ## Source files tham khảo
134: 
135: | File | Nội dung |
136: |---|---|
137: | `knowledge-base/client-first-class-map.json` | Global utility class catalog (v0.5.0, synced từ CF V2.2) |
138: | `knowledge-base/libraries/{site_id}/client-first-library.json` | Per-project variable-backed class values |
139: | `knowledge-base/libraries/{site_id}/figma-token-map.json` | Figma variable path → CF class + cssName |
140: | `agentic/specs/figma-to-client-first-mapping.md` | Quy tắc map Figma node → CF class (Sections A–G) |
141: | `agentic/prompts/read-figma-data.md` | Pre-analysis prompt, bao gồm color token catalog validation |
142: | `agentic/prompts/generate-cf-library.md` | LLM prompt tạo/update library từ Figma MCP |
</file>

<file path="agentic/memory/team-memory.md">
 1: # Team Memory
 2: 
 3: Keep this file concise. Archive older notes into `agentic/memory/archive/` when it grows beyond 200 lines.
 4: 
 5: ## What This Folder Is
 6: 
 7: This is a standalone Claude-native agentic folder for MAS V3: Figma to Webflow automation using a PM-led multi-agent workflow, Finsweet Client-First V2 rules, workspace JSON chunking, MCP-352 micro-chunking, and evidence-backed QA.
 8: 
 9: The existing files remain source-of-truth inputs:
10: 
11: - `agentic/policies/runtime-instructions.md`: original MAS V3 mandates adapted for Claude Code.
12: - `agentic/orchestration/sop.md`: four-phase workflow.
13: - `README.md`: user-facing system overview.
14: - `knowledge-base/client-first-theory.md`: Client-First theory.
15: - `knowledge-base/client-first-class-map.json`: structured Client-First class and Figma property mapping library.
16: - `scripts/*.py`: active Python workspace lifecycle tools and gates.
17: 
18: ## Hard Invariants
19: 
20: 1. Standalone baseline is mandatory: this folder must pass `agentic/evals/standalone-architecture-baseline.md`.
21: 2. Agent-system output is mandatory: `agentic/specs/agent-system-spec.md` records seed input, agent system spec, matrix, workflows, gates, and validation report.
22: 3. `@pm` is the only user-facing orchestrator.
23: 4. `@architect` owns blueprint logic and QA; it can reject builds.
24: 5. `@operator` owns Figma extraction and Webflow execution.
25: 6. `workspace/` is the operational state layer. Agents communicate through workspace artifacts, not hidden chat memory.
26: 7. Figma properties must map through `knowledge-base/client-first-class-map.json` before class decisions enter a blueprint.
27: 8. Blueprint approval is a hard stop before Webflow build.
28: 9. No silent overwrite. Existing project files and workspace state are preserved unless a documented gate approves a transition.
29: 10. Webflow external writes are high risk and require explicit workflow phase, target site/page, payload summary, and validation evidence.
30: 11. Secrets belong outside committed files.
31: 12. **MAS Build Discipline is mandatory**: every agent reads `agentic/policies/build-discipline.md` before any work. 8 patterns (D-1..D-8) cover: Write→Bash pattern, no subagents for MCP, EnterPlanMode for >5 writes, retry on bash error, caveman terse, stop after first failure, surface stand-in swap path, blocker format with retry count.
32: 
33: ## Agent Team
34: 
35: | Agent | Role | Default Access |
36: |---|---|---|
37: | `pm` | User-facing orchestrator and phase controller. | read, write plans, run safe gates |
38: | `client-first-architect` | Blueprint, Client-First class system, layout logic, QA rejection. | read, write blueprints, inspect Webflow |
39: | `figma-webflow-operator` | Figma extraction and Webflow native build execution. | read/write workspace, external Figma/Webflow when approved |
40: | `workspace-steward` | Archive, restore, state hygiene, handoff integrity. | read/write workspace lifecycle files |
41: | `qa-gatekeeper` | Deterministic validation, standalone baseline, final QA report. | read, run gates |
42: 
43: ## Current Status
44: 
45: This scaffold is self-contained. Run:
46: 
47: ```cmd
48: python scripts\gates\validate_agentic_structure.py --target .
49: python scripts\gates\run_quality_gate.py --target .
50: python scripts\gates\scan_secrets.py --target .
51: python scripts\gates\validate_agent_system_spec.py --target .
52: python scripts\gates\validate_skills.py --target .
53: python scripts\gates\validate_workspace_artifacts.py --target .
54: python scripts\gates\validate_phase_state.py --target .
55: python scripts\gates\validate_relative_paths.py --target .
56: python scripts\gates\validate_client_first_library.py --target .
57: ```
58: 
59: ## Memory Promotion
60: 
61: Promote a memory only when it has:
62: 
63: - source file or command evidence,
64: - date,
65: - owner,
66: - validation status,
67: - reason it should persist.
</file>

<file path="agentic/orchestration/retry-and-stop-conditions.md">
 1: # Retry and Stop Conditions
 2: 
 3: This spec governs stop criteria and retry limits across all compiler phases.
 4: 
 5: | Compiler Phase | Retry Limit | Stop Conditions |
 6: |---|---:|---|
 7: | CSS Contract Extraction | 1 | Output index JSONs successfully parsed, or CSS hashes missing. |
 8: | Figma Extraction | 2 | Extraction bundle successfully written, or Figma token auth failed. |
 9: | Design-System Sync | 2 | Sync report success with zero blockers, or missing design token blocks. |
10: | Component Matching | 1 | Signature report matches all primitives, or confidence < 0.60. |
11: | Figma Normalization | 1 | Normalized tree written, or raw untokenized color value exists. |
12: | Semantic IR Resolution | 1 | Tag/Class resolved tree generated, or confidence score < 0.60, or unknown class used in strict mode. |
13: | HTML Rendering & QA | 1 | HTML blueprint written, or structural errors (missing wrappers) found. |
14: | Asset manifest | 1 | manifest file generated, or alt policy gate fails (missing alt). |
15: | Chunk Slicing | 1 | manifests cataloged, or component root breached. |
16: | Webflow Native Plan | 1 | plan compiled, or destructive deletion ops found. |
17: | Webflow Deploys (Phase 11) | 3 | branch mutations serialized, or tool failure, or audit log mismatch. |
18: 
19: If any strict gate blocker is triggered, the compiler stops and reports the failure. No downstream operations may execute.
</file>

