<file path="agentic/orchestration/sop.md">
 1: # Standard Operating Procedure - HTML-First Figma-to-Webflow Compiler
 2: 
 3: This SOP governs the Claude Code-native, Python-first MAS HTML-first compiler workflow.
 4: 
 5: ## Phase 0: Setup and Audit
 6: - Steward validates/initializes workspace paths.
 7: - Ensure old files are archived.
 8: - Runs `python scripts/gates/validate_archive_cleanup.py`.
 9: 
10: ## Phase 1: CSS Contract Extraction
11: - Compile `client-first-library-contract.json` from source stylesheets.
12: - Run `python scripts/gates/validate_css_contract.py` and `validate_css_index.py`.
13: 
14: ## Phase 2: Figma Extraction
15: - Fetch Figma nodes and output `figma.node-bundle.json`.
16: - Run `python scripts/gates/validate_figma_node_bundle.py`.
17: 
18: ## Phase 3: Design-System Sync
19: - Sync Figma variable tokens with CSS Contract allowed variables.
20: - Run `python scripts/gates/validate_design_system_sync.py`.
21: 
22: ## Phase 4: Component Signature Sync
23: - Match node layouts with known components in component registry.
24: - Run `python scripts/gates/validate_component_matching.py`.
25: 
26: ## Phase 5: Figma Tree Normalization
27: - Recover generic names and auto-layouts; snap raw colors.
28: - Run `python scripts/gates/validate_figma_normalization.py`.
29: 
30: ## Phase 6: Semantic IR Resolution
31: - Resolve tag intents and Client-First class choices strictly.
32: - Run `python scripts/gates/validate_semantic_ir.py`.
33: 
34: ## Phase 7: HTML Blueprint Rendering & QA
35: - Render logical blueprint and compile physical HTML.
36: - Run `python scripts/gates/validate_html_blueprint.py`.
37: 
38: ## Phase 8: Asset Alt Policy Manifest
39: - Generate `asset-manifest.json` and validate compliance.
40: - Run `python scripts/gates/validate_asset_policy.py`.
41: 
42: ## Phase 9: Section Chunk Slicing & Benchmarks
43: - Slice page HTML into section chunks.
44: - Run `python scripts/validate_html_chunks.py` and benchmark accuracy using `validate_resolver_benchmark.py`.
45: 
46: ## Phase 10: Webflow Native Build Plan
47: - Compile section chunks into serialized native operations plan.
48: - Run `python scripts/gates/validate_native_build_plan.py`.
49: 
50: ## Phase 11: Deployment & Audit
51: - Operator requests user approval of build plan.
52: - Operator executes native mutations sequentially on target site branch.
53: - Logs every write transaction to `write-audit-log.jsonl`.
54: - Validates deployed DOM structures.
55: - Unified quality checks: `python scripts/gates/run_quality_gate.py --profile html-first`.
</file>

<file path="CLAUDE.md">
  1: # CLAUDE.md
  2: 
  3: This folder is a Claude Code-native agentic workspace for the MAS V3 Figma-to-Webflow workflow.
  4: 
  5: ## Read First
  6: 
  7: 1. Read `agentic/memory/team-memory.md` for the current agent team, invariants, and operating boundaries.
  8: 2. Read `agentic/policies/runtime-instructions.md` for the MAS V3 mandates adapted to Claude Code.
  9: 3. Read `agentic/orchestration/sop.md` before starting any Figma-to-Webflow run.
 10: 4. Read `agentic/specs/agent-system-spec.md` for the standalone agent-system contract.
 11: 5. Read `agentic/orchestration/reflection-loop.md` and `agentic/orchestration/phase-state-machine.md` before closing or changing phases.
 12: 6. Read `agentic/policies/approval-gates.md` before using Webflow, Figma, file writes, archive/restore, or any external connector.
 13: 
 14: ## Common Commands
